<p>The first resources I recommend is <a href="https://www.duolingo.com/">Duolingo</a>. I love this Application so much. The feeling while I am “playing” with this Application is incredible. There is no big vocabulary, no complicated grammar lecturing, just some daily-life sentences  practices for you at the beginning. The patten is similar with playing video games, which you will gain more badges, coins, and titles when you complete more and more challenges. There are several repeated sections in each challenge, sentence re-structuring, vocabulary matching,  sometimes you have to type down the sentence pronounces in Norwegian. Even the sections sounds like a little bit boarding if you dive into more and more challenges, but do not worry, the user interface is so amazing that encourages you complete each challenge.</p>

